trg_text: 1 World AIDS Day 2019 is an opportunity for countries globally to reflect on their respective contribution in fighting the spread of HIV and AID This year s theme recognises the essential role communities have played and continue to play in the HIV and AIDS response South Africa has been relentless in its mission to turn around the HIV, AIDS, and TB epidemics, with notable achievements which include scientific advances in HIV treatment and more people receiving antiretroviral treatmentAccess to antiretroviral therapy in the public health sector has grown from 45 500 patients in 2004 to over 4,7 million in 2019.
